      {
        "id": 2460898,
        "name": "Brian Buzzini",
        "username": "B_Buzzini",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/b_buzzini/{size}/636_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-08-06T22:59:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Thanks for the knowledge William! Just going by CT, Potinet-Ampeau most recent vintage logged in is 2011, and most of the other producers are sparse in vintages? Domaine Jean Monnier &amp; Fils does show a 15 with a couple bottles? Maybe it\u2019s just not many CT people have these wines? I\u2019d like to try some of the \u201cother\u201d producers, as Coche is too $$, and get a sense of the terroir. I just don\u2019t see any available?<br>\nBtw\u2026who lives in that house in the middle of the vineyard? <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/7/7d450e9830889c8943b674446a21b7254cad657e.gif\" width=\"18\" height=\"20\" alt=\"[wow.gif]\" title=\"wow\"></p>\n<p><img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\"></p>",
